  "source": "// Dynamic range(start, end) example for durable state maps.\n// Semantics: iterate entries in [start, end). The compiler inserts runtime\n// guards and lowers at most 64 deterministic iterations.\n// Dynamic bounds are supported on state maps.\n\nseiyaku DynamicRange {\n  state Entries: Map<int, int>;\n\n  kotoage fn bounded_range_sum(start: int, end: int) -> int {\n    let acc = 0;\n    for (k, v) in Entries.range(start, end) {\n      acc = acc + v;\n    }\n    return acc;\n  }\n}\n",
